ario, Belmond - who runs in Italy 24% of its global operations - captures 15% of the total service obtainable market. \nThe 6 properties - located in the most enchanted corners of Bella Italia - represent the most celebrated icons of hospitality. In 2016 they where responsible of a turnover of 106M EUR equal to 29% of the entire company revenue. \nAlong with the compromise-free service consistently provided throughout its hotels, the main driver of Belmond success in Italy was the regionalization of all its non-operational key functions.  \nThis business model has allowed General Management to focus on hospitality core services. In this scenario a central role has been played from a customized ERP entirely developed according the the specificity of small hotels with an average operating period of 245 days. \nSeasonality required to implement a software capable to maximize sales through a disciplined differentiation of the value proposition.", "publications/0/title": "Leveraging Big Data in the Hospitality Industry", "publications/1/publishing_date": "Sep 8, 2016", "publications/1/source": "HEC Paris Executive MBA - Major in Differentiation and Innovation through Services", "publications/1/summary": "The rationale behind Customer Lifetime Value\nThe logic of this mathematical calculation has a utilitarian purpose as its results represent a prediction of the Net Profit  generated by a continuous relationship with a customer.  In other words, Customer Lifetime Value is a powerful tool to estimate the financial value –and the cost related to generate such value— of each customer. It is a preliminary analysis that every company should follow to understand how much it can pay to acquire, retain, and develop new customers; to create value through an efficient allocation of marketing efforts and a tailor-made design products and services responding to the needs of the targeted client. CLV notably works for every relationship-based business such a services, which tend to be acquired by relying on other customer’s recommendation, but also applies to transaction-based businesses. \n", "publications/1/title": "Economics of customers and employee loyalty", "publications/2/publishing_date": "Sep 1, 2009", "publications/2/source": "The Family Business Network", "publications/2/summary": "An overview on the generation shift within Family Business.", "publications/2/title": "2020 Next Generation : Hopes, Dreams and Ambitions", "publications/2/url": "http://www.fbnasia.org/web/wp-content/uploads/2011/pdf/2020NxG.pdf", "recommendations/0/context": "Giulio managed Chanapach directly", "recommendations/0/date": "October 3, 2024", "recommendations/0/description": "I had the pleasure and luck to have Chanapach as part of my Team whilst managing Santiburi Koh Samui journey towards a product repositioning. I have always admired her energy, passion and determination to deliver exquisite Customer Experience. I would be happy in cooperating again with such a refined and detailed-oriented luxury hospitality professional.  ", "recommendations/0/name": "Chanapach Khumkhur", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Purpose-Driven Hospitality Leader | Resort Operations & Wellness | Creating Transformative Guest Experiences | Pre-Opening Specialist | Global Wellness Day® Supporter", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chanapach-khumkhur-9a900565/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA20d1EBrF4qz35NXfhtVFhywcksVffutPo", "recommendations/1/date": "October 3, 2024", "recommendations/1/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Daniele during his tenure at Hotel Splendido, a Belmond Hotel in many occasions. His natural attitude towards customer service is the result of over 20 years of hands on experience in the luxury hospitality industry and goes hand in hand with his attitude to empower his team and bring on innovative approaches to drive quick wins for each and every stakeholder involved. Working with Daniele is not only a pleasur