 Palmgren", "recommendationsReceived/12/subtitle": "Project Manager SEO and Content Management", "recommendationsReceived/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rproduction4u/", "recommendationsReceived/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAV4bZMBFlJH4LD_AnQoVrhmHAKKhJRL0cc", "recommendationsReceived/13/context": "Silvia worked with Giulio but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/13/date": "January 13, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/13/description": "Giulio is one of the best business partner I ever worked with. He has a very good mix of vision, flexibility, pride for the brand and product he represents and a natural talent to deal with people, irrespectively of their status, age and position.", "recommendationsReceived/13/name": "Silvia Tagliaferri", "recommendationsReceived/13/subtitle": "Managing Director at Cargo Plus Italy ( Subsidiary of Cargo Plus GMBH )", "recommendationsReceived/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/silvia-tagliaferri-1715765/", "recommendationsReceived/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD5LGUBENyA6zxJpYbeZTA-A2gEmX3JKhk", "recommendationsReceived/14/context": "Stefanie worked with Giulio on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/14/date": "April 27, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/14/description": "Giulio has very succesfully created an excellent business relationship with our top agents in Switzerland. He is highly respected and considered a capacity in his field of work.", "recommendationsReceived/14/name": "Stefanie Bertoneri Amrein", "recommendationsReceived/14/subtitle": "I’m a passionate traveller, world explorer, and storyteller at heart. With years of experience working in top-tier tourism companies, I’ve mastered the art of creating unforgettable, tailor-made journeys.", "recommendationsReceived/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stefanie-bertoneri-amrein-87505722/", "recommendationsReceived/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASiaRkBRfFiRTX5q98BuyIZYc3aIskcfOI", "skills/0/title": "Media Planning", "skills/1/title": "Digital Strategy", "skills/2/title": "Digital Marketing", "skills/3/title": "International Relations", "skills/4/title": "Sociology", "skills/5/title": "Political Science", "skills/6/title": "Financial Accounting", "skills/7/title": "Finacial Metrics", "skills/8/title": "Financial Analysis", "skills/9/title": "Financial Reporting", "skills/10/title": "Corporate Finance", "skills/11/title": "Performance Motivation", "skills/12/title": "Market Share", "skills/13/title": "Defining Requirements", "skills/14/title": "Interpersonal Skills", "skills/15/title": "Global Distribution Systems (GDS)", "skills/16/title": "Brand Essence", "skills/17/title": "Annual Budgeting", "skills/18/title": "Budgeting", "skills/19/title": "Budget Management", "totalExperienceYears": "21.8", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "11", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "15", "updates/0/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E12AQGo3OketfxUlQ/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/0/1520082957131?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=j62gJGQzq49gRFuPnqLVzFqEjpjSP92jIOJHkOsLGcg", "updates/0/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/heaven-leadership-my-way-giulio-stix", "updates/0/postText": "\"An did it my way\" Over the past ten years I have been exposed to myriad approaches toward leadership styles and have gleaned principles and ideologies which have contributed to my personal outlook on guiding people. Primarily between my position at Zincheria Origoni and Belmond, I have assimilated and expanded upon what I observed to be worthy and admirable traits exercised by my superiors. I have identified six positive qualities that form the acronym \"H.E.A.V.E.N.\", which I actively implement into my professional endeavors. The following terms: honestly, empathy, appreciation, versatility, engagement and network; which collectively reflect both subjective and objective qualities that advocate authority. Honesty is the subjective underpinning of any functioning professional relationship, which should be maintained at all cost. Despite keeping honesty at the forefront of virtuous and valuable relationships, especially when it can reflect negatively on you, in the long term, it will keep from even larger blunders that result from untruths. In my experience I have found even when delivering unfavorable news to my employees and colleagues, that being upfront and objective about a situation promotes greater integrity; being caught in a lie or even the most insignificant scandal will result only in a tarnished image in the eyes of your peers. Since making decisions is the overarching duty of any leader, I believe that having empathy with those involved—and those affected—will yield greater trust in the officiator and value in the decision itself. Furthermore, understanding the feelings and individual opinions of colleagues can ensure a more informed decision, and effectively allows me to relate and therefore consider the best possible outcome. As an extension of empathy, by actively showing appreciation for individual and group contributions, the leader can fuel positive interactions between associates and as a result produce superior work. While working as Sales Manager at the Four Seasons - a company who proudly claims to apply this golden rule– I recognized that when my Director rewarded my efforts I felt more inclined to continue and improve upon my work ethic. His appreciative acknowledgment encouraged my confidence and worth in my work. Everyone has something unique and important to offer –small or large—which should be highlighted and utilized by an effective leader. Objectively speaking, having versatility and general open mindedness as a leader allows for global thinking patterns and overall greater perspective. Homer famously identified Odysseus’ character with the term \"polymechanos\", which means able to perform multiple assignments. Inspired by this classic myth, I do my utmost to be flexible and adaptable, changing hats according to the objective at hand. Engagement is the ultimate initiative in any successful endeavor, whereby you must sell your team on whatever it is you’re “selling” before you can sell it in the market. Having the ability to involve colleagues in the credence of their work provides reason. Finally, the culmination of the above traits forges valuable relationships, creating a network of important contacts that have honed expertise that may prove important during your career. For a leader to have the ability to connect with other experts in their field or in tangential fields buttresses their resourcefulness as well as their credibility. While these aspects of H.E.A.V.E.N. outline the traits of a good leader, they do not necessary ensure one. Naturally, other aspects of an individual’s personality such as creativity, intuition, extroversion, organization, etc. contribute immensely to being a strong and likable leader as well; and but these qualities I mention can be developed and most importantly learned despite one’s innate character.", "updates/0/subTitle": "H.E.A.V.E.N. - Leadership, my way", "updates/0/title": "H.E.A.V.E.N. - Leadership, my way", "updates/0/type": "Article", "updates/1/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5612AQHurffhqeRCqA/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/0/1716158072941?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=ldQljIB_yxppvkPq-KrKk0nftT6dkxwQSZ4yMlT1XGs", "updates/1/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/short-tale-smart-service-recovery-giulio-stix-mba-crkjc", "updates/1/postText": "On a recent intra European flight with Swiss International Air Lines, I experienced a service recovery that totally made my day. Due to a highly congested route, my flight was strongly delayed. Based on my passenger experiemce, in such cases, the best scenario to witness is the crew airing verbal apologies. A cold comfort that vanishes once the effects of a late landing are eaten up. On this leg, while both Captain and First Officer declared to put themself at work to shorten the delay, as Service enthusiast, I started to observe how much all cabin attendants engaged in personal conversation with passengers to mitigate any possible complaint outburst. Once airborne, the increased aircraft speed was noticeable however an extremely smooth flight made the journey extremely pleasant. Being 5’o clock on a plane bound to England and with a presentation to complete, what would be better than a cup of tea? After placing my order, I started an in-depth exploration of my keynote file, finding myself on the creative side…creative ideas popped up like crazy and that mediocre file started to reflect my personality: a moment of grace that lasted about 30 minutes, at the end of which, I noticed how that cup of tea actually never reached my seat. For one or the other reason, the steward forgot to serve me and offered me a sincere apology, while I allowed myself few moments to stretch my legs. Upon getting back to my seat, that warm cup of tea was finally waiting for me and, with my pleasant surprise, it was accompanied by a chocolate bar elegantly placed on the table tray. That paid apology, was - for such a minimal glitch - not only sincere but definitely heartfelt. A tiny gesture. An attention that reminded me how much #ServiceRecovery can become a huge game changer when things don’t run as planned. Sometimes, that minimal extra mile we walk, yields a return on happiness whose effects go beyond the mere moment. What I have experienced, will definitely remain among my best travel memories and, I am sure, I shall definitely share this story - along with the fact that the flight landed with a mere 14 minutes delay - with my Team, Business Partners and Customers.", "updates/1/subTitle": "A (short) tale of a (smart) Service Recovery.", "updates/1/title": "A (short) tale of a (smart) Service Recovery.", "updates/1/type": "Article", "updates/2/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D12AQGhLH--3AmDPQ/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/0/1670673288300?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=nq3tTPjm3Lvau2Gsyog-dPiSd8blv6pjGazaQtLRZI8", "updates/2/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/being-serviceexcellence-apostle-giulio-stix", "updates/2/postText": "Throughout my entire career - spent by 4/5 within the #hospitality industry - I have enjoyed seeing me as a #serviceexcellence \"apostle\", a definition I borrowed from Boston Consulting Group (BCG) publication \"Rocket: Eight lessons to secure Infinite growth\". While the principle that service should have an important weight in every #businessmodel, it is rather difficult translate the additional money a company (or an individual) invests to make a venture successful and, ultimately, profitable for every stakeholder. I constantly take inspiration digital giants such as Apple or Amazon which - to my understanding - provide an excellent #customerjourney. Not surprisingly, the folks from Cupertino were at their end inspired by #luxuryhospitality to design what today is globally recognised as one of the most profitable #retailbusiness. On this matter, if you are fancy to deep dive into how they became champions in that field, then Carmine Gallo's book might be a great one stop read. From my personal perspective, having both covered commercial roles in #ultraluxury hospitality companies such as Belmond and Anantara Hotels, Resorts and Spas and in smaller #service companies, reading Will G. interview's on his last book carrying the very provocative Unreasonable Hospitality title, was a true confirmation of principles I have been not only put in practice during my career but also tackled as part of my HEC Paris Executive MBA major with service experts such as Roger Hallowell and Jochen Wirtz. While I do recommend in spending five minutes to go through the above, my key takeaway on Will's modus operandi totally matches the model I have applied while executing the delicate #turnaround process Emmebi Design, a luxury furniture company I was appointed CEO of. Creating meaningful connections and showing an acceptable level of vulnerability towards my speaking partners deeply served the purpose of creating the correct #teamspirit to bring the company towards the next level and to reconnect with customers abandoned along the road. All the above was spiced up with both big and tiny gestures designed to show how much the company cares for his customers and coworkers. Without getting into each of the case where walking the extra mile played a crucial role in strengthening the company's bottomline, the general idea is that I never relinquished to borrow from the #hospitalityindustry genuine and authentic care for the detail throughout the entire company value chain. An attitude that, overall, generated a tremendous impact to consolidate professional and business relationships. Obviously that is just one side of the picture: successful ventures require, along with clear financial planning, the definition of sound entry (and exit) strategies. Interested in learning more about my service-oriented vision on how to conduct business? Then let's plana one to one offline conversation.", "updates/2/subTitle": "The Service excellence apostle", "updates/2/title": "The Service excellence apostle", "updates/2/type": "Article", "updates/3/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E12AQFe49U5Z0gHQA/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/0/1520217974568?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=6H5GjJ28AzUYtKjnw2FkVGUModGZ1M6u0lkQp1N4rqI", "updates/3/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/economics-customer-employee-loyalty-giulio-stix-mba", "updates/3/postText": "The rationale behind Customer Lifetime Value The logic of this mathematical calculation has a utilitarian purpose as its results represent a prediction of the Net Profit generated by a continuous relationship with a customer. In other words, Customer Lifetime Value is a powerful tool to estimate the financial value –and the cost related to generate such value— of each customer. It is a preliminary analysis that every company should follow to understand how much it can pay to acquire, retain, and develop new customers; to create value through an efficient allocation of marketing efforts and a tailor-made design products and services responding to the needs of the targeted client. CLV notably works for every relationship-based business such a services, which tend to be acquired by relying on other customer’s recommendation, but also applies to transaction-based businesses. Calculation of the economics of customer loyalty According to James Heskett, CLV requires to define the type of customer, its average life length and its acquisition cost. Subsequently the analysis includes: the purchase pattern, the associated margin, successful referrals received by best customers and the discount rate related to the cash flows they generate. With the introduction of the idea of “type of customers” and its segmentation in 6 categories we recognize the fact that not all customers have equal present and future value. Thus customers are grouped into Antagonists, Hostages, Mercenaries, Loyalists, Viral Loyalists and Apostles/Owners. The above approach finds in Jim Sterne and Matt Cutler a similar - yet more simple - structure. According to those scholars, the CLV can be computed via the following steps. Reach: trying to get the attention of the people we want to reach Acquisition: attracting and bringing the person into the influence sphere of our organization Conversion: ensuring that customers buy when their relationship with us has been well established Retention: keeping the customers and promoting cross and up selling Loyalty: transforming customers into ‘brand advocates’ To read the full article, please PM me.", "updates/3/subTitle": "Economics of customer and Employee Loyalty", "updates/3/title": "Economics of customer and Employee Loyalty", "updates/3/type": "Article", "updates/4/image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D12AQFVxUfOdkP_0A/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/article-cover_image-shrink_600_2000/0/1529069310811?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=0-bxZ2k6LUtbcsE77Y3VxGCMjkfz3vNLrQQiYax5M2c", "updates/4/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/crafting-cutting-edge-loyalty-program-giulio-stix-mba", "updates/4/postText": "A major feat that I accomplished professionally was the successful creation an implementation of a direct marketing platform dedicated to domestic customer base for a Belmond. Prior to my appointment at Belmond in 2010, the domestic market for Italians was considerably underdeveloped, whereby Italians travelled seldom throughout their own country. The Idea I decidedly initiated a focused scheme to generate incremental sales by the use of specialized and exclusive rewards card system. Ultimately, my goal was to engender a personal relationship with Belmond members and -perhaps most importantly - a feeling of exclusivity and premier luxury through the benefits of the card offered. To achieve this goal, branding a program and executing the research to our customers was paramount in reaching our domestic clients. The nomenclature, I knew, must be not only significant, but stylized in a manner to appeal to our audience. A strong brand with a cool payoff Therefore I established the unique and intentional terminology: “adagio-vivereintensamente”, which reflects a musical significance meaning to move through life with ease yet with great intensity and profundity. I crafted this particular phraseology intentionally for two reasons: firstly, to directly appeal to Italians by using their native language instead of the global market language of English; and secondly, to reveal the manner in which the hotel brand should be understood and consumed. In a sense, Italians should search closer to home – through Belmond - to experience new levels of culture and indulgence, rediscovering Italy through deeper, more meaningful sophistication. Do people still love loyalty cards? Yes! To further underscore a level of exclusivity to our domestic clientele, I implemented a service card – the Adagio Card - offering premier access for our members by invitation only. The card was elegantly prepared, packaged as a gift and designed with a recognizable and luxurious identity. The color, a distinct, rich rubellite, reflects a jewel-like object, which holds value onto itself. Upon activation, the card would grant members special discounted rates, guaranteed room upgrades upon booking, and access to once-in-a-lifetime experiences – including entering the Sistine Chapel through its original 15th-century doors for a completely private viewing of Michelangelo’s awe-inspiring Renaissance masterpiece. After delivering the Adagio Card to our most prestigious customers, all carefully selected and invited based on our target research from our existing database, the challenge was then to further expand our clientele. Non competitive premium partners My solution was to select partnerships with comparable high-end brands, to effectively network and share targeted promotions increasing the network of the Adagio card for the Company. For example, I strategically partnered with Chopard in order to offer their customers the benefit of our luxury hotel experience for similar customer base. After four years I successfully acquired the membership of over five thousand cardholders supporting the exponential growth of Belmond’s corporate brand awareness in Italy. Remarkable financial brand awareness Results In over three years of existence, the loyalty program actively contributed in generating additional revenue and a tremendous growth of brand awareness both among its members and the strategic partners involved, leading to further cooperations and agreements that still today play an important role while developing business.", "updates/4/subTitle": "Crafting a cutting-edge Loyalty Program", "updates/4/title": "Crafting a cutting-edge Loyalty Program", "updates/4/type": "Article", "urn": "ACoAAACbrmMBK9MlO_34m-qXyvmELzmDby2MBd4", "volunteerAndAwards/0/description": "We believe that our Alumni truly understand what makes a strong EMBA candidate and what it takes to succeed in our program. We feel that there is no one better to share and assess applicants in this final stage. Your contribution and recommendations ensure that we select high-potential participants who will benefit from and actively contribute to the class.", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/month": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/year": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/industry": "Education", "volunteerAndAwards/0/is_current_position": "true", "volunteerAndAwards/0/organization": "HEC Paris", "volunteerAndAwards/0/role": "Executive Education Member of Selection Committee", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/year": "2018", "volunteerAndAwards/1/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/1/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/1/end_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/1/end_date/year": "2019", "volunteerAndAwards/1/industry": "Economic_empowerment", "volunteerAndAwards/1/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/1/organization": "Altagamma", "volunteerAndAwards/1/role": "Marketing Committee Member", "volunteerAndAwards/1/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/1/start_date/year": "2016", "volunteerAndAwards/2/description": "Otolo champions and uplifts the best industry in the world!\n\nOur mission is to serve those working in hospitality who want to see how far they can develop themselves and inspire others to do the same.\n\nWe run hospitality mentoring programmes, courses that focus on the individual and exciting events.  ", "volunteerAndAwards/2/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/2/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/2/end_date/month": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/2/end_date/year": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/2/industry": "Education", "volunteerAndAwards/2/is_current_position": "true", "volunteerAndAwards/2/organization": "People On Purpose", "volunteerAndAwards/2/role": "Business Mentor", "volunteerAndAwards/2/start_date/month": "12", "volunteerAndAwards/2/start_date/year": "2022", "volunteerAndAwards/3/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/3/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/3/end_date/month": "12", "volunteerAndAwards/3/end_date/year": "2009", "volunteerAndAwards/3/industry": "Education", "volunteerAndAwards/3/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/3/organization": "FBN (Family Business Network)", "volunteerAndAwards/3/role": "Next Generation Representative, Italy", "volunteerAndAwards/3/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/3/start_date/year": "2008", "volunteerAndAwards/4/description": "Organization of several high end fund raising activities dedicated to humanitarian causes. During my years I hold several Club and District responsibility positions including 2 terms President and Vice District Governor.\n\nMajor Services accomplished:\n•  Gala della Moda (fashion show in cooperation with Camera Nazionale della Moda Italiana, raised up to 50k EUR in one single evening)\n•  AiutAmerica (post 9/11 fund raising project dedicated to families and their relatives 20k EUR divided in two families).", "volunteerAndAwards/4/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/4/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/4/end_date/month": "7", "volunteerAndAwards/4/end_date/year": "2003", "volunteerAndAwards/4/industry": "Social_services", "volunteerAndAwards/4/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/4/organization": "Rotaract", "volunteerAndAwards/4/role": "Past 2040 Vice District Governor, Club Founder and President", "volunteerAndAwards/4/start_date/month": "9", "volunteerAndAwards/4/start_date/year": "1995", "volunteerAndAwards/5/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/5/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/5/end_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/5/end_date/year": "2009", "volunteerAndAwards/5/industry": "Environment", "volunteerAndAwards/5/is_current_position": "false", "volunteerAndAwards/5/organization": "Associazione Italiana Zincatura", "volunteerAndAwards/5/role": "Marketing Committee Member", "volunteerAndAwards/5/start_date/month": "1", "volunteerAndAwards/5/start_date/year": "2006"}$$::jsonb),
