lly in management. \n\nEndowed with excellent interpersonal skills and extremely well organized, he genuinely cares for his staff well being and always finds the time to help, guide and motivate.  \n\nHis personality and interest in people makes him a natural-born hotelier. \n\nThere is no doubt he will now succeed in Asia.", "recommendations/0/name": "Thomas Hain", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "General Manager Holiday Inn Vana Nava Hua Hin", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomas-hain/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA0AhSYBZlVEUkQlqAyr9W-bj18hP2OsklU", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Thomas managed Olivier directly", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "November 22, 2018", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I have worked directly with Olivier Masson during my assignment as the General Manager of Cape Panwa Hotel Phuket. \n\nOlivier, working as the Front Office Manager, was responsible to oversee the entire Front Office Department including Reception, Reservations, Bell Desk, Transportation and Guest Relations for the 205-keys hotel operation. \n\nOlivier had already worked several years in Thailand prior joining Cape Panwa Hotel which made him well aware of the local culture and experienced with island resort operation. Having worked for several smaller properties before made Olivier an “allrounder” type of manager who does not only look well after his own department but always strives to do the best for all areas of the hotel. He has an excellent eye for details, is very organized and always likes to get the job done the right way. He further has extensive knowledge in property management and is equally competent in Food & Beverage.  \n\nI am confident that Olivier will have a continuous successful career in Southeast Asia and I wish him well for all his future endeavors. \n", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Thomas Hain", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "General Manager Holiday Inn Vana Nava Hua Hin", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomas-hain/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA0AhSYBZlVEUkQlqAyr9W-bj18hP2OsklU", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Daniel managed Olivier directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "August 9, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Olivier is a great young guy with a good sense of humor. He’s also hard working and intelligent. It’s a pleasure to work with Olivier and he always listens and learns, but when he doesn’t agree he let you know and there follows a discussion. If he’s right he continues and if he’s wrong he drops it immediately. Always a very healthy and constructive communication when I worked with him. This is very important to me as you many times have to invent things as you go, building up a resort, F&B and an organization to support it in remote places in SEA. Olivier is very good with guests and has a genuine hospitality gene. He has the rare ability to put himself in a guests situation and act with compassion and strength when needed. I have only good things to say about him and the future is bright for this young man. I would recommend him for any junior managerial position in a smaller resort or medium sized F&B operation. Highly recommended!", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Daniel Oredsson ", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Based in Hua Hin - Hotel Management Asia (HMA)", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-oredsson-53871692/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABOu8HwBrGLSYQ9r-2dSDjBoJbesCCx2vsM", "skills/0/title": "Problem Solving & Crisis Handling", "skills/1/title": "Event & Activity Planning", "skills/2/title": "Digital Marketing & Online Sales", "skills/3/title": "Revenue & Cost Control", "skills/4/title": "Pre-Opening Management", "skills/5/title": "Team Leadership & Training", "skills/6/title": "Guest Experience & Service Excellence", "skills/7/title": "Hotel & Resort